Comment: Luke 2:1  All the people had to go ...  I turned this row and row 16 off because 'must' Obligation shouldn't set the Target Tense and Form value.  'must' can occur with any tense, so row 14 handles all tenses.
Genesis 11:4:5  We will have to move to other regions.

Clauses 1:75  If Mary reads that book, John will read this book.  If the original Time is past, the verb should be past.  Esther 2:14  If the king liked a girl, ...  This only applies if the Polarity is Affirmative.  Example with Negative Polarity: Gen. 24:8:1 If the woman won't come to Canaant with you ...  But this causes problems in Gen. 24:5 If that woman won't want to return ...
Clauses 1:76  John will read this book even if Mary reads that book.  Ruth 1:12
Clauses 1:77 John read this book so that Mary could read that book.
Clauses 1:79  Mary read this book in order to help John read that book.
Clauses 1:80  John read this book instead of reading that book.
Clauses 1:85  John caused Mary to read this book by reading that book.
